#   # Task 05: Candidate-relative position bonus and first-after-preamble boost
#   
#   ## Summary
#   
#   Change position scoring from raw line position to candidate-relative position, and add a bonus for the first candidate after filtered preamble lines (Pattern 3).
#   
#   ## Files to modify
#   
#   - `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`
#   
#   ## Dependencies
#   
#   - None (independent of other tasks, though benefits from Task 03's OCR repair)
#   
#   ## Changes
#   
#   ### 1. Change position factor to candidate-relative position
#   
#   In `extractTitleWithEmbeddings()`, the position factor is calculated at lines 772-776:
#   
#   ```typescript
#   // CURRENT:
#   const relativePosition = rs.position / lines.length;
#   const positionFactor = relativePosition < 0.5
#     ? 1.0 + 0.12 * (1 - relativePosition * 2)
#     : 1.0;
#   ```
#   
#   Change to use candidate-relative position (position among candidates that passed hard filters):
#   
#   ```typescript
#   // NEW: Use candidate-relative position instead of raw line position
#   const candidateIndex = scoredCandidates.indexOf(rs);
#   const candidateRelativePosition = candidateIndex / scoredCandidates.length;
#   const positionFactor = candidateRelativePosition < 0.5
#     ? 1.0 + 0.12 * (1 - candidateRelativePosition * 2)
#     : 1.0;
#   ```
#   
#   Note: `scoredCandidates` refers to whatever array is being iterated at this point. Check the actual variable name — it may be `candidates` or `rawScored` or similar. The key is to use the index within the candidate array that already had hard filters applied.
#   
#   **Important**: The raw `rs.position` (line position in original text) is still needed elsewhere (e.g., multi-recipe logic, structural heading detection). Only the position **factor** calculation should use candidate-relative position.
#   
#   ### 2. Add first-after-preamble bonus
#   
#   After calculating scores for all candidates but before threshold calculation, add a bonus for the first surviving candidate when it was preceded by filtered preamble:
#   
#   ```typescript
#   // Detect "first candidate after filtered preamble" pattern
#   // If the first N raw lines were all filtered (section labels, metadata, etc.),
#   // the first surviving candidate occupies the structural "title position"
#   if (scoredCandidates.length > 0) {
#     const firstCandidate = scoredCandidates[0];
#     // Check if lines before the first candidate's position were all filtered
#     const firstCandidatePos = firstCandidate.position;
#     if (firstCandidatePos > 0) {
#       // All lines from 0 to firstCandidatePos-1 were filtered/empty
#       const allPrecedingFiltered = lines
#         .slice(0, firstCandidatePos)
#         .every(line => {
#           const trimmed = line.text?.trim() ?? line.trim?.() ?? "";
#           return trimmed === "" || !passesHardFilters(trimmed);
#         });
#   
#       if (allPrecedingFiltered) {
#         firstCandidate.score += 0.08;
#         firstCandidate.thresholdScore += 0.08;
#       }
#     }
#   }
#   ```
#   
#   Place this **after** the scoring loop (around line 795) but **before** the threshold calculation (around line 903).
#   
#   Check the exact data structures — `lines` may be an array of strings or objects with `.text` property. Adapt the code to match.
#   
#   ### 3. Important edge case: position 0 candidates
#   
#   When the first candidate IS at position 0 (the common case), `firstCandidatePos > 0` is false, so no extra bonus is applied. This is correct — the position factor already gives maximum boost to position 0. The preamble bonus only fires when position 0 was filtered away.
#   
#   ## Verification
#   
#   1. TypeScript compiles without errors
#   2. For test input: `["FISH & SEAFOOD", "Halibut with Saffron Cream Sauce", "4 fillets halibut...", ...]`
#      - "FISH & SEAFOOD" should be filtered (section label)
#      - "Halibut with Saffron Cream Sauce" becomes first candidate with preamble bonus
#      - Should be selected as the title
#   3. For test input: `["Lato | Zupy | DLA 4 OSÓB | ...", "", "OGÓRKOWA ZUPA", ...]`
#      - Pipe-separated line filtered
