{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013jccVsPX2etUqTSZ5bCUoo","type":"tool_result","content":"   425→function buildCandidates(\n   426→  lines: Array<string>\n   427→): Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }> {\n   428→  const nonEmptyLines: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n   429→\n   430→  for (let i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {\n   431→    const trimmed = lines[i].trim();\n   432→    if (trimmed.length > 0) {\n   433→      nonEmptyLines.push({ text: trimmed, index: i });\n   434→    }\n   435→  }\n   436→\n   437→  const burstEnd = findBurstEnd(nonEmptyLines);\n   438→\n   439→  // Pre-join hyphen-broken lines: \"ROASTED CHICKEN WITH ROOT VEGET-\" + \"ABLES\" → single line.\n   440→  // Only applies within the candidate region (after burst end).\n   441→  for (let hi = burstEnd; hi < nonEmptyLines.length - 1; hi++) {\n   442→    if (nonEmptyLines[hi].text.endsWith(\"-\")) {\n   443→      const joined = nonEmptyLines[hi].text.slice(0, -1) + nonEmptyLines[hi + 1].text;\n   444→      nonEmptyLines[hi] = { text: joined, index: nonEmptyLines[hi].index };\n   445→      nonEmptyLines.splice(hi + 1, 1);\n   446→    }\n   447→  }\n   448→\n   449→  // Pre-merge consecutive short ALL_CAPS lines (OCR-fragmented headings).\n   450→  // When a sequence of 2+ ALL_CAPS lines each has ≤2 words and ≤25 chars, they are\n   451→  // almost certainly OCR fragments of a single heading. Merge them into one line so\n   452→  // the complete title enters the candidate pool without hitting the 3-line join ceiling.\n   453→  const capsCoalesced: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n   454→  let ci = burstEnd;\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7be50479-d25c-4053-a6c4-4687141d6376","uuid":"4459ba91-3269-4298-a8a7-adfa0f4d4fc0","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts","content":"function buildCandidates(\n  lines: Array<string>\n): Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }> {\n  const nonEmptyLines: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n\n  for (let i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {\n    const trimmed = lines[i].trim();\n    if (trimmed.length > 0) {\n      nonEmptyLines.push({ text: trimmed, index: i });\n    }\n  }\n\n  const burstEnd = findBurstEnd(nonEmptyLines);\n\n  // Pre-join hyphen-broken lines: \"ROASTED CHICKEN WITH ROOT VEGET-\" + \"ABLES\" → single line.\n  // Only applies within the candidate region (after burst end).\n  for (let hi = burstEnd; hi < nonEmptyLines.length - 1; hi++) {\n    if (nonEmptyLines[hi].text.endsWith(\"-\")) {\n      const joined = nonEmptyLines[hi].text.slice(0, -1) + nonEmptyLines[hi + 1].text;\n      nonEmptyLines[hi] = { text: joined, index: nonEmptyLines[hi].index };\n      nonEmptyLines.splice(hi + 1, 1);\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Pre-merge consecutive short ALL_CAPS lines (OCR-fragmented headings).\n  // When a sequence of 2+ ALL_CAPS lines each has ≤2 words and ≤25 chars, they are\n  // almost certainly OCR fragments of a single heading. Merge them into one line so\n  // the complete title enters the candidate pool without hitting the 3-line join ceiling.\n  const capsCoalesced: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n  let ci = burstEnd;","numLines":30,"startLine":425,"totalLines":1270}}}
